
IDEA
----
Allows you to unwind the stack to a set mark.

API:
  mark($id, BLOCK1, BLOCK2)
  unwind_to_mark($id)

mark($id, BLOCK1, BLOCK2) unconditionally runs BLOCK1 but if BLOCK1
constains code that does unwind_to_mark($id) then we unwind the stack
until the scope containing the mark command gets hit then BLOCK2 gets
executed.


Example:
--------
Prints "1"

mark($expr,{
         eval {
             sub {
                 eval {
                     sub {
                         unwind($expr);
                     }->();
                     say "0";
                 }
             }->()
           }
         }
     }
     ,
     {
         say "1";
     });


FIRST IMPLEMENTATION
--------------------
mark {
     eval {
          sub {
             unwind;
          }->()
     }
}